  storySegments:
  - text: 'As the wagon lurches again, you take a deep breath, trying to steady your
      thoughts. You need answers. The old man sitting across from you watches quietly,
      his sharp eyes flickering with a knowing light. For a moment, he smirks, almost
      imperceptibly, before leaning his head back against the bars.




'
    continueButtonText: The old man breaks the silence.
  - text: "\u201CYou don\u2019t remember, do you?\u201D he says softly, his voice
      barely louder than the rattling chains. \u201CI can see it in your eyes.\u201D\n\n\n"
    continueButtonText: 
  choices:
  - buttonText: Who are you?
    resultText: "Who am I? Just another shadow among many, caught in the turning
      wheel of this cruel machine. They call me Krelis\u2014or they did, back when
      names mattered. Now, I\u2019m nothing more than another body to work, another
      set of chains to rattle. And you? You don\u2019t even have that much, do you?
      No name. No past. Just questions."
    nextNode: {fileID: 0}
    decisionKey: 
    requiredDecisions: []
  - buttonText: Where are we going?
    resultText: "Where are we going? Somewhere dark, somewhere deep. Some say the
      mines, where the earth swallows men whole. Others whisper of pits where the
      lucky are put to work, and the rest\u2026 well, let\u2019s just say their chains
      are no longer needed. Does it matter, though? Whether it\u2019s the mines,
      the gallows, or some forgotten grave, it\u2019s all the same in the end."
    nextNode: {fileID: 0}
    decisionKey: 
    requiredDecisions: []
  - buttonText: "Why don\u2019t I remember anything?"
    resultText: "Why don\u2019t you remember? That\u2019s the trick, isn\u2019t it?
      Could be they hit you over the head before dragging you here. Could be they
      dosed you with something foul\u2014makes it easier to break a soul if you don\u2019t
      know who you are. Or maybe\u2026 maybe you chose to forget. Sometimes the weight
      of what we\u2019ve done is heavier than any chain. But don\u2019t ask me for
      the truth\u2014I\u2019m not the keeper of your past"
